article.description: Smith leads Navy to 57-47 win over Loyola (Md)
article.headline: Smith leads Navy to 57-47 win over Loyola (Md)
article.linkText: Smith leads Navy to 57-47 win over Loyola (Md)
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Worth Smith scored 20 points to lead Navy to a 57-47 win over Loyola-Maryland on Saturday. Will Kelly added 14 points and Brandon Venturini 11 for the Midshipmen (12-18, 8-10 Patriot League). Venturini to become the 22nd Navy player to surpass 1,000 points. Cam Gregory had 13 points and Eric Laster 12 for the Greyhounds (11-18, 7-11). Navy scored the first seven points of the game and when Smith scored on three straight possessions, including a pair of 3-pointers, the score was 15-5. A Venturini 3 started another run that Kelly ended with a pair of baskets to make it 24-7 just past the midway point. The Midshipmen led 32-21 at the break. Loyola scored the first seven points of the second half to close within four but Smith scored on consecutive possessions to end a 9-1 run that rebuilt the lead to 51-37 with 9:28 left. Navy made seven 3s to just one for Loyola.
